# Static-host header config (Cloudflare Pages / Netlify format).
#
# CSP frame-ancestors is the one directive browsers IGNORE when delivered via
# <meta> tag — it must come from an HTTP header. The dapp's <meta http-equiv>
# CSP at the top of tacit.html covers everything else; this file adds the
# clickjacking defense that meta can't do.
#
# 'self' (not 'none') so a hosted production deployment can still iframe its
# own /modal /preview etc. routes if it ever adds them. Tighten to 'none' if
# the dapp will never iframe itself.
#
# X-Frame-Options is the legacy equivalent for browsers that don't honor
# frame-ancestors yet (Edge < 79, IE). Modern browsers prefer the CSP one.

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors 'self'
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
